snippet: The chip maker said revenue was down 5 percent from $14.2 billion a year earlier, but it was higher than an estimate made last month.
abstract: Intel crosses an earnings bar it lowered for itself, but continues to face problems in its main market for semiconductors; chip maker says revenue was down 5 percent from $14.2 billion a year earlier.
lead_paragraph: The chip maker said revenue was down 5 percent from $14.2 billion a year earlier, but it was higher than an estimate made last month.

headline.seo: Intel Reports Third-Quarter Revenue of $13.5 Billion
headline.main: In a Slow Market, Intel Exceeds Lowered Expectations
headline.print_headline: In a Slow Market, Intel Exceeds Lowered Expectations
